From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 07:15:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Defer DualSense capture deltas until render is
 refreshed.

PipeWire can report a DualSense controller's monitor and microphone source
endpoints before it reports the speaker sink. If mmdevapi notifies applications
about that capture delta first, games can enumerate render endpoints before the
controller speaker is visible and then never bind the mono effect output for
the newly connected controller.

When the capture side has a DualSense delta and a render event is still pending,
return an empty delta with more_data set. The mmdevapi worker will process the
render event first, publish the speaker endpoint, and then come back for the
capture endpoints.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 11111111111..22222222222 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -698,6 +698,16 @@ static NTSTATUS pulse_get_endpoint_ids(void *args)
         }
 
         params->default_idx = -1;
+
+        if (params->flow == eCapture && (g_phys_event_mask & PHYS_EVENT_RENDER)
+                && (device_list_has_dualsense_audio_device(list_added)
+                    || device_list_has_dualsense_audio_device(list_removed)))
+        {
+            TRACE("Deferring DualSense capture endpoint delta until render endpoints are refreshed.\n");
+            params->more_data = TRUE;
+            goto done;
+        }
+
         pulse_wait_devices(list_added);
         pulse_wait_devices(list_removed);
 
